# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# 1. SERVICE NAMING CONVENTION:
#    - Use kebab-case: rez-api-gateway, rez-auth-service
#    - Include service type if ambiguous: rez-merchant-api, rez-customer-api
#
# 2. REGION SELECTION:
#    - oregon (us-west-2): US West coast, closest to ReZ HQ
#    - ohio (us-east-1): US East coast
#    - ireland (eu-west-1): Europe
#    - singapore (ap-southeast-1): Asia Pacific
#
# 3. PLAN SELECTION:
#    - free: Development, testing (no HTTPS custom domains)
#    - starter: Production with basic resources ($7/month)
#    - starter-plus: Production with better resources ($15/month)
#    - pro: Production with auto-scaling ($25/month)
#
# 4. SCALING:
#    - Start with minInstances: 1 for cost efficiency
#    - Increase maxInstances based on expected load
#    - Use targetMemoryPercent and targetCPUPercent for auto-scaling triggers
#
# 5. HEALTH CHECKS:
#    - All services MUST implement /health endpoint
#    - Return 200 OK when service is healthy
#    - Return 503 when service is unhealthy
#
# 6. ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES:
#    - Use sync: false for all secrets
#    - Use generateValue: true for new random secrets
#    - Use fromGroup for shared configuration
#
# 7. SECURITY:
#    - Enable security headers for all web services
#    - Use CORS configuration for API services
#    - Never commit secrets to version control
#
# 8. DEPLOYMENT:
#    - Connect GitHub repository to Render
#    - Enable auto-deploy on main branch
#    - Use deploy hooks for zero-downtime deployments
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# CUSTOMIZATION CHECKLIST
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Before deploying a new service, customize these values:
#
# [ ] Change SERVICE_NAME to your actual service name
# [ ] Update buildCommand if different from npm
# [ ] Update startCommand if different from npm start
# [ ] Set correct PORT number for your service
# [ ] Add all required environment variables
# [ ] Configure scaling based on expected traffic
# [ ] Add database configuration if needed
# [ ] Update healthCheckPath if different from /health
# [ ] Set correct region for your target audience
# [ ] Select appropriate plan based on requirements
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
